Nothing is more hectic than using a lot of utensils when preparing a dish. It can be quite a buzz kill, especially if you love cooking but hate doing the dishes. You can mix rice with steamed carrots, peas, green beans, mushrooms and corn. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Season your diced chicken with paprika then toss to coat and set aside on a plate. Step 2 Heat butter in a large pan over medium-high heat and cook the onion for 2-3 minutes, until translucent. Step 3 Add your diced chicken to the pan along with the pepper, seasoning of choice and salt. Cook your chicken for 5 minutes until it is golden on all sides, stirring regularly. Step 4 Add in your minced garlic, and cook for one minute then add your vegetables. Stir in chicken stock and rice and bring to a boil over low heat. Cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes, until rice is cooked and completely tender. Step 5 Stir in heavy cream and parmesan. Â This step is optional. Then adjust the seasoning with salt and pepper to your desired taste. Sprinkled fresh chopped parsley and enjoy with your favourite cold drink.